## Factionless roster: original creature lines (not from the source doc),
## 8 per category × 6 categories = 48 — parity with each of the other
## three factions' 48. Every line is anchored to a genuine public-domain
## mythological figure (centuries-to-millennia-old folklore, no modern
## copyrighted characterization), spanning Norse, Greek, Egyptian,
## Mesopotamian, Canaanite, Hindu, Aztec/Mesoamerican, Japanese, Yoruba/
## West African, Celtic, Slavic, Polynesian, and Maori traditions —
## deliberately avoiding Yahweh and any pop-culture-loaded reinterpretation
## (e.g. no "Morpheus," no franchise-flavored tricksters). The creature
## designs and all prose are original.

## Single-stage legendary entities from the Master OmniDex (groups 9-12 per
## category). These were missing from the original import — the sheet's roster
## is 12 groups per category: 1-8 are 3-stage evolution lines (LINES above),
## 9-12 are single-form legendaries. 71 of 72 recovered from the sheet export;
## SC-EN9 was misfiled in the sheet as "SC-E9" (typo, missing N) which is why
## the first extraction pass missed it; recovered on the second pass.
const SINGLE_STAGE_LINES: Array[Dictionary] = [
	{id="SC-EN9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Energy", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Sudarsana", desc="A discus, approximately four feet in diameter, composed of compressed solar fire and divine light. The discus spins continuously, creating a hum that resonates in the soul. It has twelve segments, each one a different color of the spectrum, and each one a different type of energy. The discus can be thrown — it travels as a projectile of pure energy that cuts through all defenses, then returns to the thrower. It generates \"divine fields\" — zones where corrupt energy is purified, where dark magic is dispelled, and where the discus's light reveals all hidden things. As a Trophy entity, it is prized for its unstoppable offensive power and its ability to purify corrupted energy. Sudarsana Cakra — the discus of Vishnu, the ultimate weapon of divine energy, the spinning wheel that destroys all evil."}]},
	{id="SC-EN10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Vajra", desc="A humanoid figure, five feet tall, with skin of pale blue that crackles with static electricity. The body has four arms — two hold \"vajra scepters\" that can channel lightning, two hold \"storm charms\" that generate weather patterns. The face is angular and focused, with eyes of ball lightning. It generates \"storm fields\" — zones where atmospheric electricity increases, where lightning strikes with precision, and where electronics are disrupted. It can \"channel\" lightning — directing electrical energy with perfect accuracy, or \"generate\" storms — creating localized weather patterns of any type. As a Utility entity, it provides electrical power, weather control, and electromagnetic disruption. Vājra — the thunderbolt, the weapon of Indra, the symbol of indestructible energy and the power of the storm."}]},
	{id="SC-EN11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Agnidevata", desc="A titan of eighteen feet, with a body of living fire — the skin is the surface of a star, the eyes are suns, the hair is a storm of flame. The body has eight arms — two hold \"sacrificial flames\" that purify through burning, two hold \"creative fires\" that forge new matter from ash, two hold \"destructive infernos\" that consume all in their path, two hold \"illuminating torches\" that reveal all hidden things. It generates \"fire domains\" — zones where combustion is instantaneous, where matter is continuously created and destroyed, where purification is agonizing, and where the entity's will is the only law of thermodynamics. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of solar fire that requires containment rather than defeat. Agni — the fire god, the first god, the deity of sacrifice, purification, and creative destruction."}]},
	{id="SC-EN12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Suryanarayana", desc="A solar deity of twenty feet, with a body of stellar plasma contained within a shell of gravitational force. The skin is visible only during flashes — between which the entity is a silhouette of absolute darkness surrounded by continuous discharge. It has eight arms — two hold the reins of seven horses of plasma, two hold \"solar discs\" that project blinding light, two hold \"heat lances\" that melt all they touch, two hold \"life-giving flames\" that restore and sustain. It rides a chariot of compressed sunlight that leaves trails of new matter in its wake. It generates \"solar domains\" — regions where the energy output of a star is concentrated, where matter is fused into new elements, where darkness is annihilated, and where life is created from raw energy. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of stellar energy that reshapes landscapes with its passing. Sūrya — the sun god, the source of all light and life, the deity whose chariot drives across the sky and whose gaze sustains the universe."}]},
	{id="SC-ET9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Mrtyudanda", desc="A staff, approximately six feet long, composed of compressed time and terminated entropy. The shaft is a timeline — visible segments showing birth, life, death, and decay, each one a different color and texture. The head is a skull of \"finality\" — a composite of all skulls, representing all deaths. The staff generates \"mortality fields\" — zones where healing fails, where regeneration stops, and where all living beings experience the weight of their own inevitable death. It can \"strike\" mortality — causing targets to experience their deaths immediately, not through violence but through the simple assertion that their time has come. As a Trophy entity, it is prized for its ability to enforce finality and its value in crafting weapons of certain death. Mṛtyu — death; daṇḍa — punishment/staff; the staff of death, the rod that delivers the final blow and enforces the law of mortality."}]},
	{id="SC-ET10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Yamaduta", desc="A humanoid figure, six feet tall, with skin of pale gray that displays visible \"soul threads\" — lines of connection between living beings and their fates. The body has four arms — two hold \"soul chains\" that bind and guide spirits, two hold \"fate scrolls\" that record the time and manner of death. The face is a mask of neutral expression, with eyes of clear crystal that see the remaining lifespan of all observers. It generates \"passage fields\" — zones where the boundary between life and death becomes permeable, where spirits can communicate with the living, and where the dying find peace. It can \"guide\" — escorting souls to their afterlife, or \"delay\" — postponing death for a time, though never indefinitely. As a Utility entity, it provides spiritual guidance, death-delay, and communication with the deceased. Yama-dūta — the messengers of Yama, the agents of death who collect souls and guide them to the afterlife."}]},
	{id="SC-ET11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Andhaka", desc="A titan of fifteen feet, with a body of absolute darkness — not black, but the absence of light, the entropy of illumination. The skin is a void that absorbs all sight, the eyes are pits of blindness that cause all who gaze upon them to lose their vision, the mouth is a maw of darkness that consumes all light. The body has eight arms — two hold \"blindness whips\" of shadow, two hold \"entropy shields\" that absorb all energy, two hold \"darkness blades\" that sever light, two hold \"void chains\" that bind and consume. It generates \"blindness domains\" — regions where light is impossible, where sight fails, where darkness is absolute, and where the entity's touch causes permanent blindness. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of entropic darkness that consumes all illumination. Andhaka — the blind demon, the son of Shiva and Parvati, born of darkness and chaos, whose touch caused blindness and whose existence was entropy incarnate."}]},
	{id="SC-ET12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Kalayavana", desc="A figure of twelve feet, with skin of weathered parchment that displays visible cracks of temporal decay. The body is emaciated, with visible bones and withered flesh, yet it moves with terrible speed and purpose. The eyes are voids of accelerated time — they show not the present but the end of all things. The body has eight arms — two hold \"time scythes\" that age whatever they touch, two hold \"decay shields\" that crumble attacks, two hold \"entropy whips\" that cause rapid deterioration, two hold \"finality chains\" that bind targets to their inevitable end. It generates \"apocalypse domains\" — regions where time accelerates to the end, where all things age and die instantly, where the future collapses into the present, and where the entity's touch is the weight of all years. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of terminal entropy that brings the end to all things. Kāla-yavana — the dark foreigner, the entropy of time made flesh, the being whose touch caused instant aging and whose presence was the end of all things."}]},
	{id="SC-G9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Merupitha", desc="A boulder, approximately five feet in diameter, of black basalt covered in Vedic inscriptions that glow with gravitational energy. The stone is the \"keystone of the world\" — it is anchored to the earth by a gravity well so strong that attempting to move it requires overcoming the weight of a continent. The inscriptions are gravity-sutras — they describe the mathematical relationships between mass, weight, and spiritual burden. It generates \"foundation fields\" — zones where gravity becomes stable and predictable, preventing phase-shifts, teleportation, and quantum uncertainty. As a Trophy entity, it is immobile and provides defensive advantages and area denial. Defeating it requires solving the gravitational puzzle of its inscriptions. Meru — the cosmic mountain, the axis mundi of Hindu cosmology, the mountain that supports the heavens and is the source of all gravity."}]},
	{id="SC-G10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Kurma", desc="A tortoise-like figure, four feet tall at the shell, with a body of compressed earth and stone — the shell is a dome of continental crust, the limbs are pillars of bedrock, the head is a boulder with eyes of magma. It has four limbs — two hold \"stability charms\" that anchor allies to the ground, two hold \"weight blessings\" that increase the mass of allies' attacks. It generates \"stability fields\" — zones where gravity is constant and predictable, where movement is steady, and where the ground cannot be shaken. It can \"support\" — creating platforms of compressed gravity that can hold any weight, or \"anchor\" — preventing allies from being moved, knocked back, or lifted. As a Utility entity, it provides defensive support, area stabilization, and gravitational anchoring. Kūrma — the tortoise avatar of Vishnu, the being that supported Mount Mandara on his back during the churning of the ocean, the foundation of cosmic stability."}]},
	{id="SC-G11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Vrtrasura", desc="A serpentine titan, thirty feet long, with a body of compressed drought-matter — the skin is cracked earth, the scales are dried riverbeds, the eyes are empty wells. The body has eight arms — two hold \"drought whips\" that drain moisture and weight, two hold \"famine shields\" that absorb energy and return nothing, two hold \"thirst blades\" that cause dehydration on contact, two hold \"blockade chains\" that prevent movement and flow. It generates \"drought fields\" — zones where gravity increases as moisture decreases, where the ground cracks and swallows, where rivers dry up, and where life withers under crushing weight. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of gravitational drought that crushes and dehydrates all in its path. Vṛtra — the serpent demon of drought, the being who blocked the rivers and caused famine, slain by Indra with the vajra."}]},
	{id="SC-G12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Hiranyaksa", desc="A titan of twenty feet, with a body of gold and iron — the skin is plated with precious metals, the eyes are molten gold, the limbs are pillars of gravitational force. The body has eight arms — two hold \"drag chains\" of compressed gravity that pull targets toward the entity, two hold \"sink hammers\" that increase the weight of whatever they strike, two hold \"depth shields\" that create zones of crushing pressure, two hold \"golden whips\" that entangle and weigh down. It generates \"sinking fields\" — zones where gravity pulls downward with irresistible force, where the ground becomes a trap, where objects are dragged to the depths, and where the entity's weight is the weight of worlds. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of gravitational supremacy that drags all things down. Hiraṇyākṣa — the golden-eyed demon, the being who dragged the earth to the bottom of the cosmic ocean, the personification of gravitational pull."}]},
	{id="SC-M9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Parijata", desc="A tree, approximately ten feet tall, with a trunk of gold and silver, leaves of emerald and ruby, and flowers of diamond and pearl. The roots extend into the ground, drawing nutrients from the earth and converting them into precious matter. The branches bear fruit of different types — some grant strength, some grant wisdom, some grant beauty, some grant longevity. The tree generates \"wish fields\" — zones where biological matter grows according to desire, where wounds heal, where youth is restored, and where the land becomes fertile. As a Trophy entity, it is prized for its fruits and its ability to generate valuable matter. Defending it requires protecting its roots, which are vulnerable to earth-based attacks. Pārijāta — the wish-fulfilling tree, the tree of heaven that grants all desires, the cosmic plant whose flowers never fade."}]},
	{id="SC-M10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Somarasa", desc="A humanoid figure, five feet tall, with skin of translucent blue that displays visible veins of silver — the circulatory system contains not blood but soma-rasa, the nectar of the gods. The body has four arms — two hold \"soma vessels\" that contain healing nectar, two hold \"distillation tools\" that purify matter into its essential form. The face is serene and youthful, with eyes of liquid silver that see the essential nature of all matter. It generates \"nectar fields\" — zones where biological matter is purified, where toxins are neutralized, where wounds heal rapidly, and where aging is slowed. It can \"distill\" — extracting the essential properties from any matter, or \"brew\" — creating potions, elixirs, and medicines from raw materials. As a Utility entity, it provides healing, purification, and alchemical support. Soma — the divine nectar, the elixir of immortality, the sacred drink that grants strength, wisdom, and healing."}]},
	{id="SC-M11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Madhukaitabha", desc="Two figures, each eight feet tall, identical in appearance — skin of blue-black chitin, eyes of burning red, bodies of impossible density. They have six arms each — two hold \"indestructible blades\" that cannot be broken, two hold \"regeneration shields\" that repair instantly, two hold \"matter whips\" that can reshape biological material on contact. They generate \"indestructibility fields\" — zones where matter becomes impossibly durable, where wounds heal instantly, where structures cannot be damaged, and where the twins' bodies regenerate from any injury. They are an Apex Heavy — a force of biological supremacy that cannot be killed by conventional means, requiring divine intervention or cosmic-level entropy to defeat. Madhu and Kaiṭabha — the twin demons of the cosmic ocean, born from the earwax of Vishnu, whose bodies were indestructible and who threatened the universe."}]},
	{id="SC-M12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Rahuketu", desc="Two entities that were once one — Rāhu is a severed head, ten feet in diameter, floating on a cushion of shadow-matter, with eyes of burning venom and a mouth of infinite hunger. Ketu is a headless body, twelve feet tall, with a neck-stump that weeps cosmic nectar and hands of shadow that manipulate matter. They generate \"eclipse fields\" — zones where matter is shadowed, where light is absorbed, where biological processes are disrupted, and where the boundary between physical and shadow matter is dissolved. They are an Apex Heavy — a force of shadow-matter that consumes light and reshapes biological forms into shadow-creatures. Rāhu and Ketu — the severed head and body of the asura who drank the nectar of immortality, the causes of eclipses, the shadow planets of Vedic astrology. SC-E9 SudarsanaEntity Sovereign Crown | Energy | Group 3 Trophy A discus, approximately four feet in diameter, composed of compressed solar fire and divine light. The discus spins continuously, creating a hum that resonates in the soul. It has twelve segments, each one a different color of the spectrum, and each one a different type of energy. The discus can be thrown — it travels as a projectile of pure energy that cuts through all defenses, then returns to the thrower. It generates \"divine fields\" — zones where corrupt energy is purified, where dar"}]},
	{id="SC-P9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Mohini", desc="A woman of supernatural beauty, five and a half feet tall, with skin of golden light that shifts through the warm spectrum. The body is adorned with jewelry of compressed illusion — necklaces, bracelets, anklets that float rather than rest on the skin. She has four arms — two hold a vessel of \"amrita\" (nectar of immortality, actually a psychic toxin), two gesture in dance poses that create mesmerizing patterns. The hair is a cascade of liquid light that moves with independent sentience. She generates \"enchantment fields\" — zones where perception is altered, causing targets to see her as their heart's desire. She can \"distract\" — drawing attention so completely that targets forget their purpose, their allies, and their own names. As a Trophy entity, she is rare and difficult to capture, but defeating her grants the victor her vessel and the ability to create compelling illusions of desire. Mohinī — the female avatar of Vishnu, the enchantress who distracted the asuras and distributed the nectar of immortality among the gods."}]},
	{id="SC-P10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Vastuka", desc="A formless entity that manifests as the \"feel\" of a place — warmth, comfort, safety, or their opposites. When visible, it appears as a humanoid figure of architectural elements: walls, doors, windows, arranged in a roughly human shape. It has four arms — two hold \"foundation stones\" that stabilize psychic environments, two hold \"roof beams\" that protect against mental intrusion. It generates \"dwelling fields\" — zones where psychic environments become stable and nurturing, promoting healing, rest, and mental clarity. It can \"haunt\" — attaching to locations and making them comforting or disturbing based on its mood. As a Utility entity, it provides psychic shelter, mental restoration, and environmental stability. Vāstu — the spirit of the dwelling, the psychic energy of a place, the being that makes a house a home or a ruin."}]},
	{id="SC-P11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Tadaka", desc="A woman of terrible aspect, eight feet tall, with skin of bark and moss that displays the faces of her victims. The body is muscular and predatory, with claws of petrified wood and teeth of fossilized bone. She has six arms — two hold \"forest whips\" of thorned vines, two hold \"psychic claws\" that tear minds, two hold \"terror masks\" that cause immediate paralysis. The eyes are pools of forest darkness that show observers their own deaths in the wilderness. She generates \"forest fear\" — zones where the wilderness becomes hostile, where paths disappear, where sounds become threats, and where the mind turns against itself. She is an Apex Heavy — a force of primal terror that consumes minds and bodies alike. Tāḍakā — the demoness of the forest, a yakshini who was cursed and became a man-eating monster, slain by Rama."}]},
	{id="SC-P12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Surpanakha", desc="A woman of distorted beauty, seven feet tall, with skin of pale green that shows the scars of ancient wounds — a nose that was cut off, ears that were mutilated, healed but never whole. The body is seductive and terrifying, with six arms — two gesture in pleading, two hold \"vengeance blades\" of psychic energy, two hold \"rejection masks\" that cause targets to experience the pain of unrequited love. The eyes are pools of green fire that show observers their own rejected desires. She generates \"rejection fields\" — zones where love becomes obsession, where desire becomes torment, where the mind fixates on what it cannot have, and where vengeance becomes the only thought. She is an Apex Heavy — a force of psychic torment that destroys minds through the weaponization of desire. Śūrpaṇakhā — the demoness of the forest, sister of Ravana, whose unrequited love for Rama led to mutilation and vengeance."}]},
	{id="SC-Q9", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Aniruddha", desc="A humanoid figure, six feet tall, with skin of liquid mercury that flows continuously without dripping. The body has four arms — two hold \"unstoppable spears\" that phase through all obstacles, two hold \"unhindered shields\" that block all attacks by existing in multiple defensive positions simultaneously. The face is smooth and featureless, with eyes of pure motion that see only movement and trajectory. It generates \"unobstructed fields\" — zones where movement cannot be stopped, where barriers are permeable, and where the entity's passage is inevitable. As a Trophy entity, it is prized for its ability to bypass all defenses and its value in crafting weapons of unstoppable force. Aniruddha — the unobstructed, the Vedic concept of that which cannot be stopped or hindered, the principle of unstoppable motion."}]},
	{id="SC-Q10", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Vayuputra", desc="A monkey-like figure, four feet tall, with fur of silver-gray that shifts through probability states — sometimes solid, sometimes translucent, sometimes invisible. The body is lean and muscular, with a tail of compressed quantum foam that can extend to any length. It has four arms — two hold \"speed charms\" that accelerate movement, two hold \"size gems\" that allow rapid scale changes. It generates \"swift fields\" — zones where movement is accelerated, where reaction time is increased, and where agility is enhanced. It can \"change size\" — shrinking to pass through cracks or growing to enormous size for combat. As a Utility entity, it provides rapid transportation, reconnaissance, and tactical flexibility. Vāyu-putra — son of the wind, Hanuman, the monkey god of speed, agility, and the ability to change size at will."}]},
	{id="SC-Q11", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Visvarupa", desc="A being of impossible scale and complexity, approximately fifteen feet tall, with a body that contains all possible forms simultaneously — it is human and animal and divine and demonic and cosmic and microscopic, all overlaid and interfering with each other. The entity has countless arms — some say a thousand, some say infinite — each one holding a different object, performing a different action, existing in a different timeline. The faces are countless — some beautiful, some terrible, some human, some alien, some alive, some dead. It generates \"cosmic vision fields\" — zones where observers see the true nature of existence, the infinite forms and infinite timelines, causing awe, terror, and transcendence. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of quantum omnipresence that exists in all states simultaneously. Viśvarūpa — the cosmic form, the universal manifestation that contains all forms simultaneously, the vision shown to Arjuna by Krishna."}]},
	{id="SC-Q12", faction="SovereignCrown", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Naranarayana", desc="Two figures, each six feet tall, identical in appearance but opposite in nature — one is solid, definite, and present; the other is translucent, uncertain, and potential. They move in perfect synchronization, their actions quantum-entangled — whatever one does, the other mirrors instantaneously across any distance. Each has four arms — one pair holds \"certainty weapons\" (definite swords, solid shields), the other holds \"possibility weapons\" (probability blades, quantum shields). They generate \"duality fields\" — zones where all things exist in quantum superposition, where certainty and possibility coexist, and where the boundary between observer and observed is dissolved. They are an Apex Heavy — a force of quantum duality that manipulates the fundamental uncertainty of existence. Nara-Nārāyaṇa — the twin sages, the dual manifestation of the supreme being, the pair that represents the quantum duality of all existence."}]},
	{id="VC-EN9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Kasha", desc="A panther-sized cat composed of liquid fire and compressed lightning, with eyes of ball lightning and claws that leave trails of fulgurite. It rides a chariot of burning bone and carbon-fiber that it manifests at will — the chariot leaves tracks of molten earth and can accelerate by converting friction into thrust. The entity can split into seven independent fireballs, each one a different thermal frequency, before recombining. It generates \"corpse-light\" — flames that burn only organic matter, leaving steel and stone untouched. As a Trophy entity, it is fast and elusive, requiring thermal-resistant equipment to capture. Defeating it grants the victor its \"fire claws\" — artifacts that can ignite organic matter with a touch. Kasha — the demon cat that steals corpses with fire, a flaming feline that rides chariots of burning bones."}]},
	{id="VC-EN10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Raiju", desc="A weasel-like creature three feet long, its body composed of compressed electrical potential that flickers in and out of visibility sixty times per second. The fur is static electricity made tangible, and it has six tails, each one a different type of electrical current. The eyes are balls of ball lightning, and its claws leave scorch marks of fulgurite. It can channel electricity through conductive materials, generate EMP bursts, and \"ride\" lightning bolts by transforming into pure electrical signal. It generates \"storm fields\" — zones where atmospheric electricity increases, making lightning strikes more frequent and electronics unreliable. As a Utility entity, it provides electrical power, electromagnetic disruption, and rapid transportation through power lines. It is temperamental and will shock allies who annoy it. Raijū — the thunder beast, companion of the thunder god Raijin, appearing as a weasel wrapped in lightning."}]},
	{id="VC-EN11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Susanoo", desc="A warrior-god, twelve feet tall, with a body of storm clouds and lightning contained within armor of compressed wind. The \"skin\" is visible only during flashes — between lightning strikes, he is a silhouette of absolute darkness; during strikes, he is blindingly bright. He carries the Kusanagi sword — a blade of pure plasma that cuts through matter, energy, and even concepts. His hair is a storm system that generates continuous thunder, and his eyes are the calm centers of hurricanes. He generates \"storm domains\" — regions where weather becomes weaponized: tornadoes spawn at will, lightning strikes with precision, hail becomes cannonballs, and rain becomes blades of ice. He can \"ride\" the wind — moving at the speed of storms, appearing as a blur of lightning and disappearing as a gust. He can \"summon\" — calling forth storm-spirits, lightning-wraiths, and wind-demons to serve him. His rage is the hurricane, his sorrow is the monsoon, and his laughter is the thunder that splits mountains. He is an Apex Heavy — a deity of destructive energy that reshapes landscapes with his passing. Susanoo — the Shinto storm god, brother of Amaterasu, slayer of Yamata-no-Orochi, master of wind, lightning, and destructive weather."}]},
	{id="VC-EN12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Kagutsupreme", desc="A humanoid figure, fifteen feet tall, composed of stellar plasma contained within a magnetic field of impossible geometry. The \"skin\" is the surface of a star — nuclear fire that burns at millions of degrees, visible only through heavily filtered perception. A crown of miniature suns orbits the entity's head, each one a different stage of stellar evolution. The entity doesn't simply generate fire — it is the concept of \"heat\" and \"light\" made manifest. It can cause spontaneous combustion in any matter by accelerating molecular vibration, generate laser beams of any frequency from its eyes, and create \"thermal singularities\" — points of infinite heat that evaporate matter into plasma before collapsing. It rides a solar flare — a wave of stellar fire that leaves auroras and electromagnetic storms. Where it walks, the ground becomes glass; where it speaks, the air ignites. It is creation through destruction, the forge that unmaking makes, and the warmth that becomes annihilation. It is an Apex Heavy — a solar deity that requires containment rather than defeat. Kagu-tsuchi — the Shinto fire god whose birth burned his mother Izanami to death, a deity of uncontrollable flame and creative destruction."}]},
	{id="VC-ET9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Shikishin", desc="A humanoid figure, four feet tall, constructed entirely of folded paper — washi skin, origami-joint limbs, and a face painted with ink lines that shift expression. The paper is \"entropy paper\" — material in a state of temporary stability, slowly decaying and regenerating. The body displays origami-fold patterns that reconfigure to create different tools. It can generate \"paper seals\" — strips that cause temporary decay or stasis (freezing in place). As a Trophy entity, it is highly sought after for its ability to generate the entropy paper, a material used for complex time-magic crafting. Capturing it grants access to this material's properties. Shikigami — the paper doll or paper man servant created by onmyōji."}]},
	{id="VC-ET10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Keukegen", desc="A small, low-lying mass of matted, dark hair and rotting moss, approximately one foot high and three feet wide, that moves with a slow, purposeful crawl. The mass emits a faint, unpleasant odor of rot and stagnant air. Within the hair, thousands of milky white eyes blink asynchronously, tracking movement. The entity generates \"disease fields\" — zones where decay accelerates for organic matter, causing immediate, fast-acting illness, flu-like symptoms, and rapid onset of chronic conditions. It can \"infect\" matter — causing food to rot instantly, clean water to stagnate, and wounds to fester. As a Utility entity, it is highly defensive and provides area denial through its decay fields. Its capture grants an understanding of biological entropy, making it a valuable resource for anti-healing and biological weapon crafting. Keukegen — the disease-spreading spirit of unknown origin, often depicted as a mass of hair or moss, bringing bad luck and illness."}]},
	{id="VC-ET11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Izanamax", desc="A towering female figure, fifteen feet tall, draped in robes of ancient, grave-wax silk that constantly sheds motes of decay. Her body is in a perpetual state of exquisite, horrifying rot — parts of her flesh are luminous with putrefaction, revealing bone beneath, yet she moves with fluid, commanding grace. Her face is a terrifying mask of sublime decay — half beautiful goddess, half rotting corpse, with eyes that are singularities of temporal decay. She generates \"Yomi domains\" — regions where the rules of the living world cease to apply, where time flows backward for the unprepared, and where decay is the only constant. She can \"curse\" life — causing accelerated aging, rapid illness, and the complete collapse of biological systems. Her touch causes the \"kiss of death\" — instant petrification of organic matter as it is propelled to the end of its timeline. She is an Apex Heavy — the queen of entropy, capable of commanding all lower entropy entities and existing as a walking, talking force of cosmic decay. Izanami — the primordial Shinto goddess of death and creation, who resides in Yomi and whose body is rotting, surrounded by the Yomi-shikome."}]},
	{id="VC-ET12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Yomotsu", desc="A force of absolute destruction that manifests as a legion rather than a single entity. It appears as a surging mass of hundreds of decomposing soldiers, all clad in rusted, ancient armor and wielding swords of brittle, fossilized bone. Each soldier is a sentient entity bound by a single entropic will. They move with terrifying coordination, overwhelming targets through sheer numbers. Their armor generates \"decay shockwaves\" — sonic bursts that shatter metal and rot wood. Their weapons inflict \"temporal wounds\" — cuts that do not bleed but instead age the affected limb by decades in seconds. The legion generates a massive \"entrenchment field\" — a zone where all matter around them begins to decay and turn to grave-earth, creating instant trenches, mud traps, and pits of quicksand. They are an Apex Heavy — an unstoppable wave of entropic force, designed to consume and decay entire city blocks. Yomotsu-Ikusa — the armies of Yomi (the underworld), commanded by Izanami to chase the living, an endless legion of the undead."}]},
	{id="VC-G9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Kaname", desc="A boulder, approximately four feet in diameter, of black basalt covered in ancient Shinto inscriptions that glow with gravitational energy. The stone does not roll or move naturally — it is anchored to the earth by a gravity well so strong that attempting to lift it requires overcoming the weight of a mountain. The inscriptions are gravity-sutras — they describe the mathematical relationships between mass, weight, and spiritual burden. It generates \"foundation fields\" — zones where gravity becomes stable and predictable, preventing phase-shifts, teleportation, and quantum uncertainty. It can \"weigh\" spirits — assessing the gravity of a being's karma and pinning them with proportional force. As a Trophy entity, it is immobile and cannot attack directly, but it provides defensive advantages and area denial. Defeating it (or rather, obtaining it) requires solving the gravitational puzzle of its inscriptions. Kaname-ishi — the keystone, a sacred rock that holds the land in place and prevents earthquakes, a foundation stone of immense spiritual weight."}]},
	{id="VC-G10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Abura", desc="A squat humanoid, three feet tall, with a head like a compressed potato and a body wrapped in a coat of woven straw that is actually composed of graviton-fibers. The entity is incredibly dense — it weighs approximately five hundred pounds despite its small size, and its footsteps leave deep impressions in any surface. It carries a small press of ancient design that can extract \"gravity oil\" — a viscous fluid that, when applied to objects, increases their weight tenfold. It can generate \"heavy fields\" — zones where gravity increases gradually, slowing movement and exhausting attackers. It can \"press\" matter — compressing objects to a fraction of their size while maintaining their mass, creating ultra-dense projectiles or storage cubes. As a Utility entity, it provides material processing, area control, and defensive support. It is slow but patient, and its oil is valuable for crafting and construction. Abura-sumashi — the oil presser, a yokai from Kumamoto Prefecture with a head like a potato and wearing a straw coat, associated with heavy labor and oil."}]},
	{id="VC-G11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Omagatoki", desc="A figure of compressed twilight, approximately eight feet tall, with a body that is not solid but a gravitational lensing of the boundary between light and dark. The entity exists only during transitional moments — dawn, dusk, eclipses — but can artificially create these conditions by manipulating local gravity to bend light. Its form is a silhouette of absolute density — where it stands, light cannot escape, creating a mobile zone of darkness that follows it. The \"face\" is a void that absorbs all illumination, and the \"hands\" are gravity wells that crush anything they grasp. It generates \"twilight domains\" — zones where the concept of \"boundary\" becomes weaponized: doors lead to wrong locations, walls become permeable, and the distinction between ally and enemy blurs. It can \"weigh\" light — increasing the gravity of photons until they cannot move, creating absolute darkness, or decreasing it until they escape into space, creating blinding illumination. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of cosmic transition that crushes everything caught between states. Ōmagatoki — the \"great darkness,\" the twilight hour when the boundary between day and night blurs, and yokai are most powerful."}]},
	{id="VC-G12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Shikome", desc="A coven of four hags, each one seven feet tall, with bodies of compressed grave-matter and faces of such ugliness that mirrors shatter in their presence. They move in synchronization, their combined mass generating a gravity well that pulls everything toward them. Their skin is a mosaic of grave-wax, tombstone dust, and rotting silk, and their hair is a tangle of iron wires and root systems. They generate \"underworld gravity\" — a crushing force that doesn't pull toward the earth but toward the concept of \"below\" — toward death, toward hell, toward the deepest pits. They can \"drag\" beings — extending their gravity wells to pull targets toward them with irresistible force, then \"weighing\" them down with the accumulated gravity of their sins and fears. They can \"dig\" through reality — using their iron-wire hair to carve tunnels through matter, space, and even time, creating shortcuts to Yomi. They are an Apex Heavy — individually powerful, but together they generate a gravity singularity that few can escape. Yomotsu-shikome — the ugly underworld women, foul hags who serve Izanami in Yomi and drag the living down to the underworld."}]},
	{id="VC-M9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Tsuchinoko", desc="A serpent, approximately two feet long and six inches in diameter, with a body of compressed biological matter that is denser than its size suggests — it weighs approximately fifty pounds. The scales are a gradient of brown to gold, with a pattern that resembles ancient script. The head is distinct from the body, with large, forward-facing eyes of amber and a mouth that can open to reveal not teeth but a second, smaller mouth. The entity can \"jump\" by compressing its body and releasing stored elastic energy, launching itself up to thirty feet in a single bound. It can \"roll\" into a wheel shape and travel at high speeds. It generates \"biological fields\" — zones where organic matter becomes malleable and easily shaped. It can \"spit\" a venom that causes temporary transformation — targets experience partial animal-features (snake eyes, forked tongue, scaled skin) that provide enhanced senses but social stigma. As a Trophy entity, it is elusive and prized for its transformative venom, which is used in high-level crafting. Tsuchinoko — the mythical fat snake, a cryptid of Japanese folklore described as a short, thick serpent with a distinct neck and the ability to jump."}]},
	{id="VC-M10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Ningyo", desc="A humanoid figure, five feet tall, from the waist up composed of pale, pearlescent skin with gill-slits along the ribs, and from the waist down a tail of iridescent scales that shift color with emotional state. The hair is a cascade of kelp-like strands that filter water and extract nutrients. The face is beautiful but alien, with large, lidless eyes of black pearl that see in the dark and through water. The entity can generate \"healing pools\" — zones of water (or water-manifested from atmospheric moisture) that promote rapid tissue regeneration, purge toxins, and restore stamina. It can \"sing\" — a harmonic resonance that accelerates biological processes: healing, growth, even evolution. It can \"transform\" — temporarily granting aquatic adaptations to allies (gills, webbed limbs, pressure resistance). As a Utility entity, it provides healing, environmental adaptation, and biological support. Its flesh is said to grant immortality, making it a target for poachers and a valuable ally for those who protect it. Ningyo — the mermaid of Japanese folklore, often depicted with the body of a fish and the head of a human, associated with storms and longevity."}]},
	{id="VC-M11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Ushiapex", desc="A titanic chimera, twenty-five feet from horn-tip to tail, with the head of a bull composed of barnacle-encrusted bone and the body of a crab-spider hybrid of chitin and coral. The bull-head has horns of compressed calcium that can drill through battleship armor, and the crab body has twelve legs ending in pincers that can shear through steel columns. The chitin is covered in a living reef — anemones that sting with neurotoxins, tube worms that sense vibrations across miles, and algae that generate oxygen and bioluminescent clouds. The entity can generate \"reef storms\" — zones where biological matter grows at impossible speeds, creating jungles of coral and shell that trap and crush entire squads. It can \"breathe\" caustic fluid — a spray of digestive enzymes that melt organic matter and leave behind mineral deposits. It can \"molt\" — shedding its chitin to create temporary decoys while regenerating a new, improved shell within minutes. It is an Apex Heavy — a walking ecosystem of biological warfare, nearly invulnerable to conventional attacks due to its symbiotic armor and regenerative capabilities. Ushi-oni — the sea ox demon, a massive chimeric beast of overwhelming physical power and biological supremacy."}]},
	{id="VC-M12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Yamata", desc="A serpentine titan of impossible scale — each head is the size of a city bus, each tail is a mile long, and the central body is a mountain of scales and muscle. The eight heads are distinct in appearance and behavior: one is scaled in crimson and breathes fire, one is armored in ice and exhales frost, one is covered in lightning rods and generates electricity, one is composed of stone and earth, one is made of flowing water, one is wreathed in poison gas, one is invisible and intangible, and one is a void that consumes light. The eight tails are equally varied — some are bladed, some are prehensile, some are club-like, some are whiplike. The entity generates \"hydra fields\" — zones where severed heads regrow within seconds, where biological matter adapts to any attack after the first exposure, and where the environment transforms to match the nearest head's element. It can \"consume\" — each head can swallow targets whole, transporting them to a digestive dimension of elemental chaos. It is an Apex Heavy — a force of nature that requires divine intervention to defeat, and even then, it always leaves a seed of regeneration. Yamata-no-Orochi — the eight-forked serpent, an immense dragon of eight heads and eight tails that demanded annual sacrifice of maidens."}]},
	{id="VC-P9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Yamauba", desc="A withered crone, five feet tall, with skin like tree bark and hair of living vines that bear poisonous fruit. Her eyes are milky white but see through deception — she perceives the true intentions and hidden fears of all who approach. She wears a robe of woven spider silk that displays the faces of her victims, still conscious and screaming. She carries a staff of human bone that generates \"hospitality fields\" — zones where she appears as a kindly old woman offering food and shelter, the illusion perfect and irresistible until the victim is within reach. Her true form emanates \"dread hospitality\" — a psychic aura that causes targets to feel an overwhelming urge to accept her offers, even knowing they mean death. She can \"cook\" memories — extracting them from victims and serving them as meals that grant her their knowledge and skills. As a Trophy entity, she is rare and difficult to capture, but defeating her grants the victor her staff and the ability to create compelling illusions of safety. Yamauba — the mountain hag, a cannibalistic witch who lures travelers with kindness then devours them."}]},
	{id="VC-P10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Zashiki", desc="A child, approximately five years old, with bobbed hair and traditional clothing, visible only to those it chooses to reveal itself to. Its skin has a faint luminescence, and its shadow is always cast in the wrong direction — toward the light rather than away. The entity manifests in enclosed spaces — rooms, vehicles, tents — and generates \"fortune fields\" — zones where probability subtly shifts in favor of allies. Attacks miss by millimeters, critical hits occur more frequently, and resources last longer than they should. The entity can \"bless\" items — temporarily increasing their effectiveness, durability, or luck. It can \"warn\" allies of danger by causing goosebumps, shivers, or sudden emotional shifts seconds before threats materialize. As a Utility entity, it cannot attack directly but provides significant tactical advantages to its team. It is shy and will abandon allies who act cruelly or dishonestly. Zashiki-warashi — the house spirit, a child-like yokai that brings good fortune and prosperity to the homes it inhabits."}]},
	{id="VC-P11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Oiwa", desc="A woman in a white burial kimono, her face partially hidden by long black hair that moves with serpentine autonomy. Where her face is visible, it is a horror of betrayal — one eye droops, the other bulges; the mouth is torn at the corners; the skin is pale with veins of black rage. She manifests through reflective surfaces — mirrors, water, glass — and can emerge from any surface that has ever reflected her image. She generates \"curse fields\" — zones where betrayal is amplified, turning allies against each other with whispers of suspicion and visions of treachery. Her gaze causes \"betrayal paralysis\" — targets freeze, unable to act, as they experience every betrayal they have ever committed or suffered simultaneously. She can \"haunt\" beings — attaching to them invisibly and causing escalating misfortune until they confess their wrongs or are driven mad. Her scream is a sonic manifestation of vengeful rage that shatters glass, ruptures eardrums, and causes permanent psychological trauma. She is an Apex Heavy — slow to manifest but nearly unstoppable once unleashed. Oiwa — the vengeful ghost of a woman betrayed and murdered by her husband, one of the most famous ghosts in Japanese folklore."}]},
	{id="VC-P12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Psyche", stages=[{name="Kayako", desc="A woman in a blood-stained white dress, her body broken and twisted into impossible angles — neck snapped, limbs bent backward, spine curved like a question mark. She moves not by walking but by crawling, dragging her broken body with jerky, insect-like movements that produce a distinctive death-rattle from her crushed throat. Her hair is a living mass of black tendrils that extend across floors, walls, and ceilings, reaching for prey with grasping, pulling motions. She is bound to locations but can extend her influence through any space that has experienced violence or rage. She generates \"grudge fields\" — zones where accumulated resentment and anger become tangible, manifesting as ghostly hands that pull at targets, whispers that drive them to violence, and visions of their own deaths. Her touch causes \"grudge infection\" — a psychic poison that causes the target to become a carrier of her rage, spreading violence and hatred to those around them until they are consumed by it. She is an Apex Heavy — relentless, patient, and inescapable once her attention is fixed. Kayako — the grudge ghost, a woman murdered in a fit of rage whose spirit is bound to the place of her death, crawling down stairs with a death-rattle."}]},
	{id="VC-Q9", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Izuna", desc="A fox the size of a wolf, with fur of silver-white that shifts through the visible spectrum like an oil slick. Its most distinctive feature is its tail — not one but a fractal branching of tails that splits into smaller tails, each one a different quantum state of the entity. The eyes are prisms that show multiple angles simultaneously, and its footprints exist in superposition — they appear in multiple locations at once until observed. The entity can \"possess\" probability — altering the likelihood of events by shifting its own quantum state. It can phase through solid objects by existing in a different phase state, and create \"probability clones\" — multiple versions of itself that exist simultaneously and operate independently before collapsing back into one. As a Trophy entity, it is elusive and difficult to capture, but defeating it grants the victor a \"probability tail\" — an artifact that grants limited quantum-shifting abilities. Izuna — the fox spirit of Izuna Mountain, associated with shamanism, possession, and the ability to shift between worlds."}]},
	{id="VC-Q10", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Kudagitsune", desc="A fox the size of a rat, with fur of reddish-gold and eyes of amber that see in all directions simultaneously. Its body is capable of compressing to fit through any opening — keyholes, cracks, pipes — by shifting its quantum state to occupy less space than its mass should allow. It can \"ride\" signals — transforming into electrical or photonic form to travel through wires, radio waves, or light beams. It generates \"spy fields\" — zones where it can observe without being observed, existing in a quantum state where it is present but undetectable. It can \"whisper\" information across distances by quantum-entangling with a target, allowing silent communication. As a Utility entity, it provides intelligence, reconnaissance, and communication support. It is loyal to its master but mischievous, occasionally altering messages for its own amusement. Kuda-gitsune — the pipe fox, a tiny fox spirit that lives in bamboo pipes and serves as a spy and messenger."}]},
	{id="VC-Q11", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Tamamo", desc="A woman of impossible beauty, approximately five and a half feet tall, with nine tails that fan behind her in a cascade of quantum probability — each tail is a different timeline, a different version of the entity across parallel worlds. The tails display scenes from alternate realities: some show her as empress, some as destroyer, some as savior, some as prisoner. Her eyes are golden with slit pupils that contain miniature galaxies, and her smile is the moment before quantum collapse — all possibility and no certainty. She can \"split\" herself into nine independent entities, each one a different aspect (warrior, scholar, seductress, destroyer, etc.), that operate simultaneously across a battlefield. She can \"rewrite\" probability — causing certain outcomes to become inevitable and others to become impossible within her domain. She can \"consume\" timelines — absorbing the potential futures of targets, leaving them with only one possible path: defeat. Her voice is polyphonic, speaking in multiple timelines simultaneously, and her laughter causes localized reality fractures. She is an Apex Heavy — a cosmic trickster of devastating power and infinite cunning. Tamamo-no-Mae — the nine-tailed fox, a legendary kitsune who served the emperor and was revealed to be a cosmic fox spirit of immense power."}]},
	{id="VC-Q12", faction="VeiledCurrent", category="Quantum", stages=[{name="Sutoku", desc="A figure in imperial robes of black and gold, approximately six feet tall, but existing in multiple states simultaneously — he is simultaneously alive and dead, human and tengu, emperor and exile, present and absent. The robes display scenes from his life and afterlife playing simultaneously: his coronation, his exile, his death, his transformation, his vengeance. His face is a shifting composite — sometimes a handsome young emperor, sometimes a withered corpse, sometimes a tengu with a long nose and red face, sometimes a void. He generates \"transcendence fields\" — zones where binary states collapse into superposition, making it impossible to determine if targets are alive or dead, present or absent, real or illusory. He can \"curse\" probability — causing targets to experience all possible misfortunes simultaneously across multiple timelines. He can \"ascend\" — shifting to a higher quantum state where he is immune to physical harm but can still influence the world through probability manipulation. His voice is a chorus of his multiple states speaking in imperfect unison, and his gaze causes quantum decoherence — forcing complex systems to collapse into their simplest, most damaged state. He is an Apex Heavy — a being who has transcended death and become a force of cosmic injustice. Emperor Sutoku — the emperor who became a veng"}]},
	{id="WA-EN9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Energy", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Atumprime", desc="A towering humanoid of living plasma contained within a skeleton of gold-alloy struts. The head is a Benben-shaped capacitor that stores infinite solar potential. Its skin is a photosphere that emits all frequencies of electromagnetic radiation simultaneously, visible as a blinding white-gold aura. The hands can project focused beams that rival stellar flares or gentle warmth that incubates life. A serpent of pure energy coils around its form — the uraeus, representing sovereignty over all energy states. When it opens its mouth, it speaks in the language of nuclear fusion, causing nearby matter to undergo spontaneous transmutation. Atum — the primordial creator god who arose from the primordial waters on the Benben stone; the self-created source of all solar energy."}]},
	{id="WA-EN10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Energy", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Heka", desc="A serpentine entity of braided energy currents, its body a double helix of opposing polarities — red destructive current and blue restorative current. The head is a cobra hood made of sparking plasma, the eyes twin capacitors that store spell-potential. It wears no armor; its scales are hexagonal energy shields that deflect physical and energy attacks by converting them into stored magic. The tongue is a filament that can inject or extract energy from any system. It speaks in words that manifest as temporary reality alterations — saying \"burn\" causes combustion, saying \"heal\" triggers cellular regeneration. Its presence causes dormant energy sources to activate and active ones to amplify. Heka — the personification of magic and medicine, the divine force that animated the universe; the word \"heka\" means the first work, the activation of potential."}]},
	{id="WA-EN11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Energy", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Rasun", desc="A colossal falcon-headed humanoid of living stellar matter, its body a contained fusion reaction that burns at millions of degrees. The head is a raptor's skull of neutron-dense gold, the eyes twin suns that emit killing light. The body is armored in solar flare plates that erupt periodically, creating zones of absolute thermal destruction. A solar disc — the Aten — hovers above, connected by beams of concentrated energy that serve as both crown and weapon. The barque of millions of years manifests as a hovering chariot of plasma that trails cometary fire. At nightfall, its form shifts to Ram-Headed Ra, the underworld aspect, burning with baleful green fire that consumes souls rather than matter. Ra — the supreme sun god, creator and king of the gods; the falcon-headed deity who sails the sky by day and the underworld by night in his solar barque."}]},
	{id="WA-EN12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Energy", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Khepribug", desc="A titanic scarab of living emerald and gold, its carapace a curved solar collector that focuses dawn's first light into a weapon. The body is a biological reactor that converts waste and decay into pure energy — it grows stronger as the battlefield becomes more devastated. The head is a beetle's mandibles capable of crushing energy fields and redirecting their power. The legs are pillars of solidified dawn-light that leave tracks of new growth and renewal. It pushes before it a sphere of compressed stellar matter — the newborn sun — that rolls across terrain, annihilating everything in its path with heat and radiation. When threatened, it can curl into its carapace, becoming an impenetrable dome that radiates healing energy to allies within. Khepri — the scarab-faced god of the rising sun, rebirth, and creation; the self-created deity who pushes the sun across the sky like a dung ball."}]},
	{id="WA-ET9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Entropy", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Nephthys", desc="A shrouded figure of absolute black that absorbs all light and sound, its form only discernible by the negative space it creates. The veil is woven from the fabric of event horizons, patterned with silver hieroglyphs that describe every death that has ever occurred. Beneath the shroud, hints of a feminine form composed of dying star matter flicker in and out of perception. Its hands are skeletal with fingers that unravel into threads of void that stitch wounds closed by removing the concept of injury. Where it walks, footprints fade before they form, and it leaves behind only the memory of absence. Nephthys — the goddess of death, night, and protective darkness; sister of Isis, guardian of the dead, mistress of the hidden and the transformative void."}]},
	{id="WA-ET10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Entropy", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Mafdet", desc="A sleek cheetah-humanoid of black marble and gold inlay, its spotted pattern formed by patches of accelerated decay. The claws are scalpels of degenerate matter that can excise corruption with surgical precision. The eyes are amber sensors that detect lies and imbalances in any system. A collar of braided rope around its neck can extend into lassos of entropic force that bind and unravel threats simultaneously. It moves in stuttering frames, existing between moments to strike at causal weak points. Where it runs, the ground behind it ages centuries in seconds, while the path ahead is cleared of all obstacles through targeted dissolution. Mafdet — the goddess of justice and execution, depicted as a cheetah or lynx; the swift punisher who protects against snakes and scorpions, representing entropy as righteous dissolution."}]},
	{id="WA-ET11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Entropy", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Anubis", desc="A towering jackal-headed entity of black obsidian and funeral gold, its body perfectly preserved yet radiating the promise of inevitable decay. The head is a canine skull of polished jet with eyes of silver flame that see the death-state of all things. The body is mummiform, wrapped in bandages of woven entropy that simultaneously preserve and doom. In one hand it holds the scales of judgment — one pan holds the Feather of Maat, the other generates a miniature black hole that consumes the unworthy. The other hand holds the golden key to the tomb, which can lock any entity into a state of suspended dissolution. It is surrounded by a retinue of canopic jar drones that collect and store the essential elements of fallen enemies. Anubis (Anpu) — god of mummification and the afterlife, the jackal-headed guardian who weighs hearts and guides souls; the original psychopomp before Osiris rose to prominence."}]},
	{id="WA-ET12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Entropy", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Apophis", desc="A serpent of impossible scale, its body a chain of event horizons that stretches across the horizon. The scales are fragments of destroyed realities, each one a window to a universe that no longer exists. The eyes are absent — blind pits that absorb all information, including the concept of sight. The mouth is a vortex of absolute entropy that unravels causality, consuming not just matter and energy but the history and possibility of whatever enters. It wears no armor; its body is the armor of void against which nothing persists. Where it passes, the sand does not merely die — it never was. The air around it screams with the sound of unmaking. It is the end that awaits all things, the serpent that will eventually devour the sun, the stars, and finally itself. Apep (Apophis) — the serpent of chaos, the eternal enemy of Ra, the personification of dissolution and non-existence; the snake that seeks to devour the sun and return all to primordial void. OMNI DEX: RACES ROSTERTotal Races20Race IDRace NameFaction AffinityCore Stat BonusDescription1Ashen ChoirRaceVeiled CurrentInfluence +20% Resonance +15%Sorrow Amplification2ChronarchsRaceSovereign CrownCooldown Reduction +20% Resonance +10%Micro-Rewind3ColdmarrowRaceWildlands AscendantDamage Mitigation +25% Control +10%Freeze Aura4PulsebornRaceSovereign CrownMomentum +25% Cool"}]},
	{id="WA-G9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Gravity", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Akertwin", desc="Two massive lion statues of black granite and gold, fused back-to-back at a singularity point. The eastern lion is armored in rising-sun plating, the western in sunset-copper. Between them, they generate a gravitational anomaly that bends light into a perpetual horizon. Their manes are composed of captured meteorites orbiting in stable patterns. When they roar in unison, they create a gravitational wave that flattens structures and compresses matter into neutron-dense cubes. Their eyes are eclipses — one solar, one lunar — that manipulate tidal forces. Aker — the double lion god of the horizon and the earth's gateway; the guardian of the eastern and western horizons where the sun enters and exits the underworld."}]},
	{id="WA-G10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Gravity", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Shu", desc="A lithe figure composed of compressed atmosphere and magnetic field lines, visible only by the refraction of light through its body. It wears armor of floating geometric plates held in position by localized gravity wells. The head is crowned with ostrich feathers that generate hurricane-force winds. Its breath is a controlled gravitational wave that can push objects into orbit or pin them to the ground with crushing force. The hands manipulate atmospheric pressure, creating vacuum bubbles or dense air shields. It leaves no footprints — it walks on manipulated air density, and its presence causes weather systems to organize into geometric patterns. Shu — the god of air and sunlight, who holds Nut (sky) above Geb (earth); the separator of cosmic bodies through atmospheric and gravitational force."}]},
	{id="WA-G11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Gravity", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Nutsky", desc="A titanic feminine form arched over the battlefield like a living planetarium, her body composed of star-stuff and dark matter. The skin is a map of the night sky, constellations moving across her surface in real-time. The belly is a gravitational well that captures incoming projectiles and crushes them into singularities. The hair is a cascade of comet trails and nebula mist that generates localized gravity storms. She is supported by Shu-atmospheric columns at her hands and feet, creating an arch of absolute gravitational dominance. Stars along her body can be plucked and thrown as gravity bombs. Her mouth opens to the void between worlds, capable of swallowing entire formations into digestive pocket dimensions. Nut — goddess of the sky, stars, and cosmos; the arched body of the heavens who swallows the sun each evening and births it each dawn."}]},
	{id="WA-G12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Gravity", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Gebearth", desc="A mountainous entity of living rock and fertile soil, green-skinned where exposed, armored in continental plates that shift with tectonic force. The body is prone, forming a landscape rather than standing — hills, valleys, and rivers across its back. The eyes are pools of magma that weep lava tears. The mouth is a cave system that speaks in the rumble of earthquakes. The hands can press into the ground and cause fault lines to open, swallowing enemies or launching them with seismic force. Snakes of pure gravitational force emerge from its skin, constricting targets with crushing G-forces. Where it rests, the ground becomes an extension of its will, rising into fortifications or collapsing into traps. Geb — god of the earth, vegetation, and snakes; the green-skinned lord of the ground who causes earthquakes and grows all life from his body."}]},
	{id="WA-M9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Matter", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Khnum", desc="A colossal ram-headed entity seated at a wheel made of compressed planetary core material. Its body is a fusion of living muscle and ceramic armor, the joints showing spinning pottery mechanisms. The hands are skilled artisan's tools that can reshape molecular bonds with a touch. A kiln-furnace replaces its stomach, glowing with the heat of creation. It wears an apron of woven Nile silt that transmutes into any material needed. The horns are spiraled repositories of every substance in existence, from hydrogen to transuranic elements. Where it works, the ground rises into sculpted forms that gain semi-autonomous life. Khnum — the ram-headed god who shapes humans from clay on his potter's wheel; the master craftsman of biological and mineral matter."}]},
	{id="WA-M10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Matter", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Ptah", desc="A mummiform figure of green-skinned living bronze, wrapped in bandages of woven schematics. The head is skull-like with eyes of emerald that project holographic blueprints. The hands are multi-tool appendages that can reconfigure into any instrument — welders, lasers, molecular assemblers. A beard of braided conductive material hangs from its chin, serving as an antenna for matter-resonance frequencies. It carries a staff that was once the Djed pillar, now converted into a matter-phase inducer. Where it works, raw materials self-assemble into complex structures following its projected designs. Ptah — the creator god of Memphis, patron of craftsmen and architects; the divine engineer who shaped the world through thought and creative speech."}]},
	{id="WA-M11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Matter", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Sokar", desc="A massive falcon of living metal and preserved flesh, its wingspan casting shadows that materialize into solid matter. The body is a fusion of gold, electrum, and meteoric iron, the feathers individually forged and articulated. The eyes are rubies that emit laser-precision matter-scanning beams. The talons can crush tanks or delicately manipulate atomic structures. It wears a collar of hieroglyphic inlays that program matter-transmutation protocols. The beak is a plasma cutter capable of slicing through dimensional barriers. When it screeches, the sound waves cause molecular bonds to resonate and shatter. It perches on a ziggurat of compressed grave goods — weapons, jewelry, and artifacts that it can animate as drone extensions. Sokar (Seker) — falcon god of the Memphis necropolis, patron of craftsmen working in precious metals; the guardian of the secret chambers where bodies were prepared for eternity."}]},
	{id="WA-M12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Matter", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Tefnut", desc="A towering lioness-headed entity of living water held in shape by surface tension and will alone. The body is translucent, showing schools of bioluminescent microorganisms that serve as its immune system and sensory network. The mane is a storm cloud that rains various substances — healing water, corrosive acid, binding resin, or catalytic solutions. The eyes are whirlpools that can draw matter into crushing density. The hands are shaped like lotus blooms that open to release matter-restructuring enzymes. It wears armor of calcified shells and coral that grows and repairs itself. Where it walks, the ground becomes marsh that spawns biological constructs — fungal soldiers, plant-based barriers, bacterial swarms that consume specific materials. Tefnut — goddess of moisture, dew, and rain; the twin of Shu, lioness-headed source of all water and biological matter."}]},
	{id="WA-P9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Psyche", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Baofra", desc="A massive falcon with a luminous human face and wingspan of twenty meters, each feather a solar panel etched with consciousness-code. The body is armored in gold plating that reflects the viewer's deepest thoughts. It carries a miniature sun between its talons that pulses with collective memory. The eyes are portals to a shared dreamscape. When it screeches, the sound rewires neural pathways in listeners, granting temporary telepathic links. Its flight leaves trails of liquid thought that pool into mirrors showing alternate timelines. The Ba — the aspect of the soul represented as a human-headed bird; here fused with Ra's solar barque to create a trophy entity of transcendent consciousness."}]},
	{id="WA-P10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Psyche", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Sia", desc="A floating brain of crystallized thought matter encased in a gold-wire mesh that pulses with synaptic lightning. The surface is mapped with neural pathways that glow in sequence as it processes information. Tendrils of fiber-optic nerve tissue extend outward, connecting to any data source. The \"face\" is a holographic display showing constantly shifting hieroglyphic equations. It communicates directly to the mind, bypassing language. When threatened, it projects confusion fields that scramble enemy targeting systems and cause weapons to misfire by rewriting their users' understanding of their function. Sia — the personification of perception, knowledge, and insight; the divine intellect that guides the heart and tongue."}]},
	{id="WA-P11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Psyche", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Osiris", desc="A towering green-skinned deity seated on a throne of fused bone and black stone, wrapped in bandages of living shadow. The head is crowned with the Atef — white ostrich feathers mounted on rams' horns, crackling with psychic authority. The eyes are pools of the Duat's darkness that strip away mental defenses with a gaze. One hand holds the crook of dominion over minds, the other the flail that shatters egos. The chest bears the wound of Seth, eternally bleeding green ichor that spawns thought-forms. Its voice resonates in the skulls of all within range, rendering commands impossible to disobey. The throne is surrounded by psychic shock troops — fragments of consumed personalities that serve as extensions of its will. Osiris — god of the afterlife, resurrection, and the underworld; the green-skinned lord of the dead who judges souls and grants rebirth."}]},
	{id="WA-P12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Psyche", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Set", desc="A bestial giant of crimson hide and black armor, the head an elongated snout of unknown animal origin — the Set animal. Its body is a storm system of raw psychic turbulence, visible as lightning patterns under translucent skin. The eyes are yellow voids that induce madness on contact. It wields a was-scepter of compressed thunderheads that strikes with both physical and mental force. The armor is asymmetrical and jagged, reflecting its nature as the lord of disorder. Where it stands, reality becomes uncertain — colors invert, sounds precede their sources, and causality loosens. It is surrounded by a whirlwind of debris that moves to its chaotic will, each piece a projectile guided by telekinetic rage. Set (Seth) — god of chaos, storms, disorder, violence, and foreigners; the red-haired lord of confusion who slew Osiris and contests Horus."}]},
	{id="WA-Q9", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Quantum", role="Trophy", stages=[{name="Mekhet", desc="A floating eye the size of a chariot wheel, suspended in a gyroscopic ring of superconducting gold. The iris is a mandala of shifting probabilities, the pupil a black hole that records everything it witnesses. Seven smaller eyes orbit the main body like electrons, each observing a different dimensional frequency. The sclera is carved with hieroglyphs that rewrite themselves based on what is observed. It emits a beam that forces quantum superposition to collapse, making all possible states of a target manifest simultaneously. The eyelids are armored shutters that, when closed, create zones of absolute uncertainty where physics fails. Mekhet — the \"Divine Eye,\" one of the Egyptian words for the Eye of Horus/Ra; the all-seeing quantum observer that collapses possibility into reality."}]},
	{id="WA-Q10", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Quantum", role="Utility", stages=[{name="Heh", desc="A kneeling figure of polished obsidian with arms raised in perpetual supplication, but the arms extend into infinite regression, each hand holding a smaller version of itself. The body is hollow, containing a pocket dimension of endless recursive space. The head is a Mobius strip of gold that rotates without moving. It generates fields of temporal stasis where time loops infinitely, useful for preserving allies or trapping enemies in eternal moments. The raised hands create quantum barriers that exist in all possible states simultaneously, making them impenetrable by any single form of attack. Heh (or Hehu) — the personification of eternity, depicted as a kneeling man with raised arms; one of the Ogdoad, representing endlessness and the infinite."}]},
	{id="WA-Q11", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Quantum", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Thothscribe", desc="An immense ibis-headed entity of silver and lapis lazuli, its beak capable of writing reality-altering equations in the air. The body is a library of compressed dimensions, its robes made of papyrus scrolls containing every possible future. The head is crowned with a lunar disc and crescent that phase through all states simultaneously. One hand holds a palette that mixes pigments of probability — dip in blue for likely futures, red for unlikely, black for forbidden. The other holds a reed pen that writes events into existence before they occur. Its eyes are pools of starlight that see all quantum branches at once. When it writes, the air crystallizes into deterministic pathways that force reality to conform. Thoth — god of wisdom, writing, magic, and the moon; the ibis-headed scribe who maintains the universe's records and knows all that is, was, and will be."}]},
	{id="WA-Q12", faction="WildlandsAscendant", category="Quantum", role="Apex", stages=[{name="Maat", desc="A colossal winged figure of gold and white stone, suspended in a perfect lotus position. The wings are geometric constructions of light that span fifty meters, each feather a law of physics made manifest. The head is featureless save for a single vertical eye of absolute clarity. The body is perfectly symmetrical, divided down the middle into matter and antimatter held in impossible balance. It wears no armor — its skin is the fabric of cosmic order, impenetrable by chaos. In one hand it holds the Feather of Truth, a quantum stabilizer that forces all nearby probability to resolve into lawful outcomes. Its presence suppresses all randomness, making enemy attacks predictable and ally actions perfectly efficient. Maat — goddess of truth, balance, order, harmony, law, morality, and justice; the feather against which hearts are weighed, the fundamental structure of reality."}]},
]

const FACTIONLESS_LINES: Array[Dictionary] = [
	{id="FL-EN1", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Misiyn", desc="A stout, broad-shouldered figure crackling with restrained static, knuckles wrapped in strips of storm-scarred leather. Distant thunder answers every footstep, though the sky above stays clear."}, {name="Miseir", desc="Lightning now arcs constantly between its clenched fists, and each step leaves a scorched footprint of fulgurite glass. Storm clouds gather directly overhead wherever it stands."}, {name="Misax", desc="A titan wreathed in a permanent thunderhead, its heartbeat audible as rolling thunder for miles. Where it strikes the ground, lightning forks in the shape of a hammer and the air itself rings like struck bronze."}]},
	{id="FL-EN2", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Miumenel", desc="A slim, falcon-eyed figure whose skin holds the dull warmth of embers banked overnight — never quite going out. A faint solar disc rides just above its brow, more suggestion than object."}, {name="Miumenor", desc="The disc has lifted free and now orbits its head slowly, throwing a thin corona that lengthens every shadow it crosses into the shape of a noon sundial, regardless of the actual hour."}, {name="Miumenun", desc="A towering solar herald whose disc has become a second sun low on the horizon, casting two shadows from everything nearby — one true, one running fast-forward through the day that hasn't happened yet."}]},
	{id="FL-EN3", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Gorraling", desc="A softly luminous figure wrapped in layered silk-like light, retreating half a step whenever looked at directly, as if shy of being seen fully."}, {name="Gorradiv", desc="The light has taken on a woven, mirror-bright quality, throwing back fractured reflections of whoever stands nearest — never quite their true expression."}, {name="Gorrasav", desc="A sunrise given a walking shape, so bright that looking at it directly leaves afterimages that linger for days, each afterimage whispering encouragement in a voice the observer almost recognizes as their own, kinder."}]},
	{id="FL-EN4", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Briret", desc="A squat, sturdy figure wreathed in a low blue flame that never spreads to whatever it stands on, turquoise scales flickering across its forearms like dying coals."}, {name="Brirum", desc="The blue flame has climbed to a full mantle, and the turquoise scales have hardened into overlapping plates that chime like glass when it moves, a sound like a hearth about to become a wildfire."}, {name="Briror", desc="An old-fire god scaled to a bonfire the height of a building, turquoise-plated and burning a blue so deep it reads as cold — anything it touches either catches instantly or frosts over, with no middle setting."}]},
	{id="FL-EN5", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Oruluxa", desc="A broad-shouldered figure with an axe of grey stormcloud slung over one shoulder, hair that stands on end even in still air."}, {name="Oruluxiel", desc="Twin axes now, and small forks of lightning jump between its fingers when it clenches a fist, thunder arriving a half-second sooner than it should."}, {name="Oruluxon", desc="An oak-rooted storm titan, its axes now full lightning bolts that never fully leave its hands, thunder arriving before the swing does — cause and effect have stopped agreeing on the order of things nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-EN6", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Kelil", desc="A double-headed figure carrying a smoldering carved staff, each head watching a different direction at once."}, {name="Kelan", desc="The staff now trails a ribbon of static-charged smoke, and each head speaks half a sentence the other completes, always about a storm arriving elsewhere."}, {name="Kelex", desc="A twin-visaged storm-king whose staff has become a spinning column of ball lightning, both heads speaking in perfect unison now about storms that have already happened somewhere else and are still deciding to happen here."}]},
	{id="FL-EN7", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Quelumenil", desc="A lean, sun-bright figure with a wheel-shaped halo that turns slowly whether or not there's any wind."}, {name="Quelumenan", desc="The wheel-halo has grown spokes of hard white light, and every few turns throws a spark that becomes, briefly, a second small sun hovering nearby before fading."}, {name="Quelumenex", desc="A midsummer titan crowned in a wheel of solid light the size of a chariot, throwing off sparks that become short-lived suns, each one aging a small patch of ground through an entire season before it gutters out."}]},
	{id="FL-EN8", faction="Factionless", category="Energy", stages=[{name="Mitel", desc="A hummingbird-quick silhouette, iridescent feathers at the shoulders catching light that shouldn't be there in the shade."}, {name="Mitor", desc="The feathers have become a mantle of live embers shaped like wings, and its footsteps leave scorched hummingbird-prints that flare and vanish."}, {name="Mitun", desc="A war-sun titan robed in wings of solid flame, casting a light so directional that it creates a false noon in whichever direction it's decided the day should go."}]},
	{id="FL-ET1", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Quelnen", desc="A gaunt, ash-grey figure that moves like time-lapse decay — flowers wilt and paint peels in a slow ripple around its footsteps. Its eyes are twin hourglasses, sand perpetually falling."}, {name="Quelnir", desc="The decay ripple has widened into a visible field; metal rusts and wood rots on contact within several paces. Its hourglass eyes have cracked, sand leaking as fine grey dust that never depletes."}, {name="Quelnax", desc="A colossal herald of ending, trailing a wake where entire seasons pass in seconds — crops ripen and rot, structures age to ruin. Its voice is the sound every clock makes in its final tick, heard simultaneously by everyone nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-ET2", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Vavel", desc="A gaunt, veiled figure who leaves faint grey handprints on anything she brushes past — the exact texture things have after long neglect."}, {name="Vavor", desc="The veil has become seven layered veils, each one shed only in a place utterly out of sight, and what's beneath is a little less finished each time."}, {name="Vavun", desc="The Queen of a going-nowhere-fast, seven veils now permanently in motion around a form that gets vaguer the closer it's looked at, and every door it passes through remains permanently a little bit ajar, letting the cold out of somewhere else."}]},
	{id="FL-ET3", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Masil", desc="A once-beautiful figure kept carefully in three-quarter profile, the unseen side clearly do not want to be looked at yet."}, {name="Masan", desc="Turning further reveals patches of quiet decay held together by will alone; she apologizes for it in a voice that is still, somehow, kind."}, {name="Halsiex", desc="She has stopped turning away. What was hidden is now simply what she is: a slow, dignified ruin that has made peace with rot, and offers the observer the same peace, whether or not they want it."}]},
	{id="FL-ET4", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Nonoyn", desc="A bone-thin figure in a paper collar, eye sockets a little too wide, always mid-smile."}, {name="Noneir", desc="The bones have gone slightly translucent, faint marigold light behind the ribs, and the smile has widened past what a jaw should allow."}, {name="Nonax", desc="A skeletal lord of the deepest floor, wreathed in owl feathers and dim marigold light, whose smile has become the only expression left available to it — worn permanently over whatever it used to feel."}]},
	{id="FL-ET5", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Tuumis", desc="A crow-shouldered woman-shape at the edge of vision, always exactly three crows in the air nearby, never more, never fewer."}, {name="Tuumar", desc="The three crows have started landing in the exact spots someone is about to fall, an instant before they fall there."}, {name="Tuumoth", desc="A battlefield made person, crow-cloaked and washing bloodied cloth in a stream that runs backward — whoever recognizes their own garment in her hands has already, in some sense, finished today."}]},
	{id="FL-ET6", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Rerynis", desc="A charcoal-dark shape that seems to absorb the light around lanterns rather than merely stand in shadow."}, {name="Rerynar", desc="The dark has thickened into a kind of smoke-armor, and small lights nearby gutter and require re-lighting twice as often as they should."}, {name="Rerynoth", desc="A black-god given full shape, wearing an armor of extinguished light — every flame within its reach burns a shade dimmer permanently after it passes, as if it kept a little of the light for itself."}]},
	{id="FL-ET7", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Toelel", desc="A restless figure wrapped in nine skirts of wind-torn cloth, always slightly out of sync with the actual weather."}, {name="Toelor", desc="The nine skirts have become a standing dust-devil that follows her exactly, tearing loose whatever wasn't already settled."}, {name="Toelun", desc="A tempest-queen who arrives as her own weather front, nine winds at once, each one carrying off something different — memories, roof tiles, second chances — and depositing them somewhere she'll never say."}]},
	{id="FL-ET8", faction="Factionless", category="Entropy", stages=[{name="Halluxil", desc="A rangy, sharp-snouted figure with reddish hide and an unplaceable, slightly wrong gait, like a familiar animal walking with borrowed legs."}, {name="Halluxan", desc="The wrongness of the gait has spread to its whole silhouette, which now seems assembled from several different creatures that don't quite agree on scale."}, {name="Halluxex", desc="A storm-red usurper-shape, composite and confident, whose every part is recognizable and whose whole is not — proof, it seems to argue by simply existing, that a good enough story doesn't need to make sense."}]},
	{id="FL-GR1", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Esharen", desc="A slick, eel-smooth humanoid that never quite touches the ground, hovering in a shallow well of bent space that pools like water around its feet. Its voice carries a faint, layered echo, as if speaking from underwater."}, {name="Esharir", desc="The gravity well beneath it has deepened into a visible depression that objects slowly slide toward. Its skin has taken on a deep-sea bioluminescence, patterns pulsing in rhythms too slow for human speech to match."}, {name="Esharax", desc="A vast, tidal presence that bends the ground into a permanent basin, pulling loose objects and unbraced people toward its center in slow, inexorable orbits. It speaks in pressures felt in the chest rather than sound heard by the ear."}]},
	{id="FL-GR2", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Reoril", desc="A stooped, immensely broad-shouldered figure perpetually bracing against a weight nobody else can see, knees never quite straightening."}, {name="Reoran", desc="The unseen weight has started leaving actual impressions in solid stone beneath its feet, deep enough to hold rainwater."}, {name="Reorex", desc="A world-bearing titan frozen mid-effort, the ground around it permanently sloped inward as though everything nearby has already started, very slowly, to roll toward where it kneels."}]},
	{id="FL-GR3", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Calten", desc="A slim, bark-skinned figure with roots instead of trailing hair, always standing at a slight, deliberate lean, as if propping something up."}, {name="Caltir", desc="The lean has become permanent and structural — nearby trees list gently toward it, and the space around its shoulders reads subtly taller than everywhere else."}, {name="Caltax", desc="A forest-father holding an invisible ceiling at arm's length, the space beneath him stretched a little higher than physics would otherwise allow — proof that the sky was, once, much closer, and someone had to move it."}]},
	{id="FL-GR4", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Drana", desc="A round-eyed, fanged little figure that always stands in a personal patch of damp ground, however dry the surroundings."}, {name="Draniel", desc="The damp patch has become a standing puddle that mirrors clouds not actually in the sky, and small hailstones fall only within its reach."}, {name="Dranon", desc="A mountain-shaped rain-lord whose personal weather never leaves him, dragging a slow, localized deluge that pools uphill, against every rule water is supposed to follow."}]},
	{id="FL-GR5", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Seenis", desc="A reclining-postured figure who always seems slightly sunken into whatever surface he's on, as though standing were an ongoing negotiation."}, {name="Seenar", desc="The sinking has become visible subsidence, soft depressions following him a few steps behind like slow footprints in solid rock."}, {name="Seenoth", desc="An earth-father laid nearly flat by his own gravity, the ground for yards around him gently bowl-shaped, water and small objects alike drifting, unhurried, toward whichever way he's currently facing."}]},
	{id="FL-GR6", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Halrynen", desc="A broad, patient figure who seems to be carrying an enormous, invisible flat weight balanced across both shoulders."}, {name="Halrynir", desc="The invisible weight now visibly bows the shoulders, and small stones nearby have begun to arrange themselves in the cardinal directions around her feet."}, {name="Halrynax", desc="A world-mother bearing the whole flat weight of everywhere at once — a held breath given permanent shape, holding the horizon level purely through the effort of never once putting it down."}]},
	{id="FL-GR7", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Velen", desc="A river-quiet figure whose footsteps sound like a distant waterfall no matter the terrain."}, {name="Velir", desc="Small pools now form in her wake and drain toward her rather than downhill, and the waterfall-sound has grown loud enough to mask other noises nearby."}, {name="Velax", desc="A river-mother whose passage bends water itself against slope and sense, every stream nearby politely rerouting to pass beneath her feet, as though she were the actual lowest point in the world."}]},
	{id="FL-GR8", faction="Factionless", category="Gravity", stages=[{name="Lorarel", desc="A weathered, sea-worn figure who leans into a wind that isn't blowing, boots always damp regardless of the ground."}, {name="Loraror", desc="The lean has become a permanent list, like a ship keeling in harbor, and the damp has spread into a thin standing tide around each footprint."}, {name="Lorarun", desc="A harbor-god keeled permanently to port, dragging a private tide that rises and falls to a moon only he can feel, pulling loose anything nearby that was never properly anchored down."}]},
	{id="FL-MT1", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Ruvil", desc="A weathered, bearded figure built from interlocking river stones that shift and resettle with each movement, mortared by threads of living root. Where it kneels, small stones nearby roll toward it and fuse in."}, {name="Ruvan", desc="The stone-and-root body has grown a second, denser layer of bedrock plating, and the roots now bear small pale flowers that open and close with its breathing. Its footsteps leave patches of accelerated, unnatural growth."}, {name="Ruvex", desc="A mountain given a walking shape, its bedrock body layered with visible strata recording ages it has witnessed. Forests sprout and mature in the wake of its passing, and its voice is the deep groan of tectonic plates settling."}]},
	{id="FL-MT2", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Leithis", desc="A compact, tool-handed figure whose fingers end in small, precise implements rather than nails, always mid-adjustment of something unseen."}, {name="Leithar", desc="The tool-fingers have multiplied and specialized, and faint construction-lines — chalk marks for a building not yet begun — trail from its hands onto every surface it touches."}, {name="Leithoth", desc="A craftsman-creator whose every gesture leaves behind faint architectural blueprints scored into stone, wood, and skin alike, as though it is quietly, patiently, drafting the next version of everything nearby."}]},
	{id="FL-MT3", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Nexelyn", desc="A four-armed, soot-marked figure constantly measuring things with tools that vanish the moment they're set down."}, {name="Nexeleir", desc="Two more arms have grown in, each holding a different half-finished instrument, and its measurements have started applying themselves — walls straighten, joints tighten, unbidden."}, {name="Nexelax", desc="The architect of everything given eight arms and eight tools, each one mid-strike on a different unfinished corner of reality, quietly correcting the geometry of whatever it walks past whether asked to or not."}]},
	{id="FL-MT4", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Sevel", desc="A hard-eyed, iron-scarred figure who leaves a faint rust bloom on anything metal he brushes past."}, {name="Sevor", desc="The rust bloom has become a living patina that creeps and forms crude, useful shapes — a hook, a blade, a hinge — from whatever metal is nearby."}, {name="Sevun", desc="An iron lord whose passage forges and unmakes metal in the same breath, leaving behind half-finished tools and weapons that seem to know, on their own, what they're for."}]},
	{id="FL-MT5", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Kilet", desc="A skirted figure whose hem seems to be woven from something that moves on its own, though it's too dim to see clearly."}, {name="Kilum", desc="The hem is unmistakably alive now, a slow tangle of small serpentine shapes, and small stones and roots gather at her feet as if paying respects."}, {name="Kilor", desc="A mother-of-all given a skirt of living serpents, giving birth to small stones and thorned growths with every slow step, the ground around her turning fertile and dangerous in the same instant."}]},
	{id="FL-MT6", faction="Factionless", category="Matter", stages=[{name="Musil", desc="A moss-shouldered figure whose skin shows faint cracks like dry riverbed, always slightly warm to a temperature the air doesn't explain."}, {name="Musan", desc="The cracks have deepened into fissures that occasionally show a soft green glow beneath, and small growths sprout wherever she rests a hand."}, {name="Kezaex", desc="A world-mother whose cracked, warm body is quietly, continuously growing something new in every fissure — moss, root, ore — patient proof that matter, given enough time in her presence, prefers to become something alive."}]},
